Package: uefi-boot-helper
Version: 1.0.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: important
Architecture: all
Depends: efibootmgr, gzip (>= 1.0), gzip (<< 2.0)
Enhances: linux-image, initramfs-tools
Maintainer: Alejandro GonzÃ¡lez <alejandro.gonzalez.correo@gmail.com>
Description: Kernel image and initramfs hooks for updating the ESP and EFI boot entries
 This package maintains the EFI system partition and EFI boot manager entries updated
 whenever a new kernel image package is installed or a new initial ramdisk is generated,
 so that the UEFI boot manager always tries to boot the latest installed kernel and
 ramdisk first.
 .
 If you remove this package, the UEFI boot manager and ESP contents will no longer be
 updated automatically, which may lead to booting previous versions of the kernel and
 the initial ramdisk.
